      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "chopped"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add onion and garlic and sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add chili flakes, cumin, and brown sugar and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add black olives, soy sauce, apple cider vinegar, and water and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook for 10-15 minutes or until the sauce has thickened slightly.",
    "Stir in chopped cilantro and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve hot over rice or with crusty bread."
